args: Lord Ieyaaasu! Where have you run off to?
Yup. And luckily for us, we're headed\nin the exact opposite direction today.\nI think we're safe to mosey.
Splendid. I would've hated to postpone\nmy observation of the lifeguards.
Gotta hand it to that butler—he's a lot\nwilier than he looks. Persistent, too.\nThe guy is EVERYWHERE.
Truly. And he's only redoubled his efforts\nto locate us with each passing day. I do\nfeel a bit guilty leading him around...
But not guilty enough to allow an entire\nsummer to be wasted on frivolous revelry.

Sounds like you guys have it rough.
I guess survey tours aren't quite as
fun as they sound, even if you ARE
checking out a seaside paradise.
Anyway, that's enough commiserating.\nWe're nearly there.
Aaand we made it. Hey, bro!\nThese are the people I told you about!
Hey, Setta and company!\nWe've been waiting for you. Welcome!
You wanted to ask about Fellista Beach's\nlifeguards, yeah?
Correct. Might I add that I am humbled you\nwould take time away from your duties to\nindulge my request? This is invaluable.
Don't sweat it. It's my pleasure. Now,\nto get right into it, our number one job\nis accident prevention.
Which means our priority is keeping\na constant watch on the shore.
That much is identical to our own system.\nUnfortunately, we still see incidents occur\nfrom time to time.
Right. Which brings me to the next most\nimportant part of our work: getting help to\nthose who need it as swiftly as possible.
And to do that, we use the seacutter.
Put simply, it's a vehicle that runs on the\nwater. Our friends in Chanzelia unearthed\none and restored it to working order.
Seeing as Chanzelia is landlocked, they\nwere kind enough to loan it to us in\nexchange for data from its use here.
I see. It does seem rather fascinating.\nThe chassis design in particular sparks\na certain natural curiosity.
Eyyy, this guy gets it! Ooh, I know.\nWanna take it for a spin?
So this is the seacutter... Sitting astride it\nconjures to mind my equestrian escapades.

Funny you should mention that—the
Chanzelian engineers said they based
their redesign on horseback riding.
Now, let's take her out. Ready?
It's so FAST! Agile, too! If it responds\nso readily to my commands... Hyah!
It feels like an extension of my body. Heh,\nI'm reminded of the night I raced my horse\nup the mountain pass behind the manor!
Someone sure is acting like a kid on\nDragonyule. You're adorable, Ieyasu.
I confess, it's rather thrilling! This\nseacutter might even outpace a dragon.
You think that thing's faster than ME?\nIf that's a joke, I'm not laughing.
Erm! It was in no way my intention to cast\nany doubts or aspersions on your abilit—
Can it! Whatever your ＂intention,＂ it's\nsomething one race will settle. Now take\nyour weird un-horse and let's do this!
Talky time's over, pal. First one to that\nlittle island and back wins. Ready? GO!
Marishiten! Agh... I suppose I'll only\nmake this worse if I ignore her. Apologies,\nsir. I'll be borrowing this awhile longer!
Huh? Oh—whoa. There he goes.\nWell, uh... YOU GOT THIS, IEYASU!
There, see? I'm way faster than that rickety\nantique.
*huff* *huff* Is that any surprise?\nI'm on a vehicle I only just discovered,\nwhereas you've been flying since birth.
But without question, this victory is yours.\nNow, I should like to put this whole\nconversation behind us and move on.
Fine by me. No point dragging it out\nwhen I'd just beat you every time. Maybe\nthis'll teach you to watch what you say.
Yes, yes. You've made it abundantly clear\nthat you're—
I was watching the whole time.\nIeyasu was holding back. I could tell!
He's REALLY strong. If he was trying\nhis hardest, he would never lose!\nRight, Ieyasu?!
That's not true! Ieyasu's WAY stronger\nthan you!
If he didn't trip at the very start, he'd have\nbeaten you, EASY! He only held back\n'cause you have seniority... *sniff*
WAAAAAH! Ieyasu would never lose for\nreal!
(Ha ha, that brought me back. The time I\nspent studying at the dojo with Botan feels\nso nostalgic now.)
(I'd lost a sparring match, and Botan came\nto my defense just like Setta. Then she\nmade me promise to win the next bout.)
You truly think I'm capable, Setta?
Doy! You've GOT this, Ieyasu.\nJust give it one more go!
A tempting thought. Back then, my place in\nthe hierarchy prevented me from asking for\na rematch, but now...
Ha ha, I'm just talking to myself. I think\nI would like to reclaim my honor after all.
I can't very well let your faith in me go\nmisplaced. Now, Marishiten, I challenge\nyou to a rematch!
Oh ho! Bold of you to pick a fight with\nthis particular dragon. But then again,\nit's not altogether surprising you would.
Either way, you're on. And you know I'm\nnot gonna be holding back, so you better\ncome at me with everything you've got.
I wouldn't dream of doing otherwise.\nWatch closely, Setta. Here I go!
There's that fire I knew you had.\nReminds me of when we first swore a pact.
The day I said that world domination was\nincidental, and asked your aid in protecting\nthe peace?
I thought you were out of your gourd. Still\ndo, really. But I knew you were the kinda\nguy who fought hardest for others.
...Which explains why you're faster this\ntime around. I'm giving it all I've got,\nand you still passed me!
The occasional upset is what keeps an\nuneven match fun. Plus, I'm under explicit\norders from Sazanka to cut loose a bit.
So I'm very sorry, but I'll be winning this\nround. I hope you won't take it personally!\nHAAAAH!
I can do this! As long as I maintain this\npace until the end, victory is—
I've finally found you, Lord Ieyasu!
The BUTLER?! We're out on open water\nhere! And I thought this guy was persistent\nBEFORE!
No butler worth his salt would fail to\nreceive his masters' guests because of a\nlittle thing like the ocean being in his way!
Now, let us return forthwith, Lord Ieyasu. A\nmost resplendent party awaits y—waugh?!
Sir! No... When he extended his hand to\nme, it caused his dinghy to capsize!
Rgh... This is no time for vain competition.\nForgive me, Setta.
My good man, I'll pull you up now!\nGive me your hand!
Soft as ever, Ieyasu. But I hate a fight\nwith no ending. I'm finishing this race out.
...So I'm afraid it was my loss yet again,\nSetta. My apologies.
I swore to rise to meet your expectations,\nbut fell short. Forgive me this betrayal.
Aw, it's fine. Keep your chin up, Ieyasu.
Sure, it's a little frustrating. But you were\ncool out there when you rescued that guy.
Plus, your seacutter technique was on full\ndisplay. Even from here, you looked like a\npro!
He's right. It was an impressive display.\nEven among us lifeguards, there aren't\nmany who could match it.
Besides, wasn't the whole point of your\ntrip to see how they do rescue stuff here?\nI'd say you checked that box off just fine.
You're terribly kind, Setta. I thank you for\nyour thoughtful words. Heh... You've once\nagain reminded me of the past.
One of my dear friends growing up would\noften console me much as you just did.\nTruly, I'm blessed with excellent friends.
Yeah? You...do know flattery won't get\nyou anything out of me, right? Not that\nI'm complaining; I'm just...kinda broke.
Ha ha. Kind AND modest! I shall have to\nwork harder than ever to ensure I don't\ndisappoint you again.
And, out of respect for the butler's tenacity,\nI will make a point of attending at least a\nfew more social engagements as well.
That sounds less scary than having him\nchase you all the way out into the ocean\nagain. I'm sure you'll survive.
I shall endeavor to! I plan to redouble my\nefforts, both in work and in enjoying this\nsummer with you, Setta. On to the next!
